

Q2==> String is immutable because of security and concurrency, synchronize caching and loading.

* Difference between String and String Builder.

==> StringBuilder is used to represent a mutable string of characters. Mutable means the string which can be changed.
    So String objects are immutable but StringBuilder is the mutable type. It will not create a new modified instance
    of the current string.

* Some of the methods of String Class.
==> 1.toLowerCase()
    2.toUpperCase()
    3.subSequence()
    4.subString()
    5.toString()